@startuml image-upload-flow
!theme vibrant

title Clothing Image Upload & AI Processing Flow

actor User
participant "React\nFrontend" as Frontend
participant "Wardrobe\nService" as WardrobeSvc
participant "MongoDB\nGridFS" as GridFS
participant "Remove.bg\nAPI" as RemoveBG
participant "RabbitMQ" as Queue
participant "Image\nProcessor\nWorker" as Worker
participant "Google\nVision AI" as VisionAPI
database "MongoDB" as DB

User -> Frontend: Upload clothing photo\n(JPG/PNG, <5MB)
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Frontend: Validate image:\n- File size\n- Format\n- Dimensions

Frontend -> WardrobeSvc: POST /api/wardrobe/clothing\nmultipart/form-data
activate WardrobeSvc

WardrobeSvc -> GridFS: Store original image
activate GridFS
GridFS --> WardrobeSvc: originalImageId
deactivate GridFS

WardrobeSvc -> RemoveBG: POST /removebg\n{image_file}
activate RemoveBG
RemoveBG --> WardrobeSvc: Image with background removed
deactivate RemoveBG

WardrobeSvc -> GridFS: Store processed image
activate GridFS
GridFS --> WardrobeSvc: processedImageId
deactivate GridFS

WardrobeSvc -> DB: Create clothing item\n{userId, imageIds, category}
activate DB
DB --> WardrobeSvc: clothingItemId
deactivate DB

WardrobeSvc -> Queue: Publish to image_processing_queue\n{itemId, imageId}
activate Queue

WardrobeSvc --> Frontend: 201 Created\n{itemId, imageUrls}
deactivate WardrobeSvc

Frontend --> User: Show uploaded item\n(AI processing...)
deactivate Frontend

Queue -> Worker: Consume message
activate Worker

Worker -> GridFS: Fetch image
activate GridFS
GridFS --> Worker: Image buffer
deactivate GridFS

Worker -> VisionAPI: POST /v1/images:annotate\n{image_content}
activate VisionAPI
VisionAPI --> Worker: AI Analysis:\n- Labels\n- Colors\n- Object detection
deactivate VisionAPI

Worker -> Worker: Parse AI response:\n- Extract category\n- Identify colors\n- Determine style\n- Calculate confidence

Worker -> DB: Update clothing item\n{aiAnalysis: {...}}
activate DB
DB --> Worker: Updated item
deactivate DB

Worker --> Queue: ACK message
deactivate Worker
deactivate Queue

note right of VisionAPI
  AI identifies:
  - Category (92% accuracy)
  - Primary & secondary colors
  - Style (casual/formal/athletic)
  - Fabric type
  - Suitable occasions
end note

note right of RemoveBG
  Background removal
  creates clean product
  images for outfit display
  
  Credits tracked:
  49 remaining
end note

note left of Worker
  Asynchronous processing
  prevents blocking user
  during AI analysis
  
  Typical processing:
  2-5 seconds
end note

@enduml
